records.addlTxt:
Defendant Chad M Lodhi in court with attorney Samuel Bendict for  Jorge R Fragoso.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court vacates prior convictions as the defendant has completed the drug treatment contract. State moves to orally amend the DOV dates on count 6 and count 7. Court grants.  Defendant enters a guilty plea as to counts 1, 6 and 7. Counts 2, 3, 4 and 5 are dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

(Attorney Benedict to provide letter with any jail credit within 14 days)

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   AS TO EACH COUNT, CONSECUTIVE TO EACH OTHER

3 MONTHS STRAIGHT TIME

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS PROBATION

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with the victims unless they consent and approved by the agent

RESTITUTION:  TO BE HELD OPEN

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);
DRGOD SURCHARGE $10.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Restitution hearing scheduled for October 13, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
